## Coding Patterns

### Component Architecture
- **"use client" directive** on all interactive components (most components)
- **Server components** for thin wrappers (e.g., `/app/ai-resources/page.tsx`)
- **Client components** for interactivity, animations, state management
- Page-specific components live in `/app/[page]/components/`
- Shared components live in `/components/`

### Data Management
- **Static content** centralized in `data.ts` files within feature directories
- TypeScript interfaces defined at top of data files
- Export constants: `DISPATCH_WEEKS`, `MODELS`, `TOOLS`, `TASK_RULES`, `QUIZ_QUESTIONS`, `PROMPTS`, `LEARNING_LEVELS`
- No external APIs or databases currently used
- LocalStorage used for bookmarks in Navbar

### Animation Patterns
- **GSAP with @gsap/react** for scroll-triggered animations
- **useGSAP hook** with `scope` parameter for cleanup
- **ScrollTrigger plugin** registered at component level
- Common animation pattern:
  ```tsx
  useGSAP(
    () => {
      gsap.from(ref.current, {
        y: 30,
        opacity: 0,
        duration: 0.75,
        ease: "power2.out",
        scrollTrigger: { trigger: ref.current, start: "top 88%" },
      });
    },
    { scope: sectionRef }
  );
  ```
- Stagger animations for lists using class selectors (`.pl-card`, `.lp-card`)
- VideoHero uses frame sequence with canvas rendering (192 frames)

### Styling Patterns
- **Inline style objects** for all component styling
- Design tokens as constants:
  ```tsx
  const labelStyle: React.CSSProperties = {
    fontFamily: "var(--font-dm-sans), sans-serif",
    fontSize: "11px",
    fontWeight: 500,
    letterSpacing: "0.2em",
    textTransform: "uppercase",
    color: "#9A8E7A",
  };
  ```
- Mouse event handlers for hover states (no CSS :hover)
- Conditional styling based on state
- Responsive values using `clamp()` for typography

### Routing & Navigation
- **Next.js App Router** - file-based routing
- **Path alias**: `@/*` imports from root
- Navbar active prop for current page highlighting
- Smooth scroll with offset calculation for section navigation
- Section IDs: `dispatch`, `finder`, `quiz`, `prompts`, `learning`

### Special Patterns
- **Iframe pattern** for legacy HTML content (book summaries, intellect articles)
- **IntersectionObserver** for active section tracking in SectionNav
- **LocalStorage** for bookmark persistence (key: `colloque_bookmarks`)
- **Clipboard API** for copy-to-clipboard functionality
- **Zoom/pan pattern** for image viewing (PromptLibrary cheat sheet)

## What to Avoid

- **Do not use CSS modules** - this project uses inline styles exclusively
- **Do not use styled-components** - not part of the stack
- **Do not use Tailwind classes for complex layouts** - use inline styles
- **Do not create new CSS files** - all styling is inline or in globals.css
- **Do not use external CSS-in-JS libraries** - not part of the stack
- **Do not add new animation libraries** - GSAP and Framer Motion are already used
- **Do not use "use client" unnecessarily** - only for interactive components
- **Do not hardcode color values** - use design tokens or defined palette
- **Do not break the inline styling pattern** - maintain consistency
- **Do not add new font families** - Cormorant Garamond and DM Sans only

## Conventions

### File Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `SectionNav.tsx`, `VideoHero.tsx`)
- **Pages**: `page.tsx` (App Router convention)
- **Data files**: `data.ts` (lowercase)
- **Static assets**: kebab-case (e.g., `cheatsheet-hires.webp`)
- **Frame sequence**: `frame_####.jpg` (4-digit zero-padded)

### TypeScript
- **Strict mode enabled** - all types must be defined
- **Interface definitions** for data structures at top of files
- **Type exports** from data files for reuse
- **React.CSSProperties** type for inline style objects
- **No `any` types** - use proper TypeScript typing

### Component Organization
- **Imports at top** - React hooks, then libraries, then local imports
- **Type definitions** after imports
- **Constants** after types
- **Component function** after constants
- **Helper functions** inside component or before main component
- **useGSAP** calls after state initialization
- **Return statement** at end

### Code Style
- **Inline styles** as objects, not strings
- **Mouse handlers** for all interactive states (hover, focus)
- **Conditional rendering** with ternary operators
- **Early returns** for edge cases
- **Comment sections** with visual separators (e.g., `// в”Ђв”Ђ Section в”Ђв”Ђ`)

### Section IDs (for navigation)
- AI Resources: `dispatch`, `finder`, `quiz`, `prompts`, `learning`
- Used by SectionNav for scroll tracking
- Must match in data and components

